rComments: Ah, where to begin. I found prof Aucoin just OK. She's super nice (& perhaps this would be different if we were IRL), but her class just dragged. I took the class as an elective (I was interested in the content), but idk. Was just so boring. We talked about urban gardens for so long. But I give her 3/5 (she's very understanding/accommodating).

Have taken many classes with Prof Aucoin. A really kind and intelligent person who knows a lot. She will help you out as much as you can, over email or in office hours. Her assignments are always really interesting. She provides the most interesting readings and bibliography. 2 short ethno assignments, 1 paper, 1 midterm, 1 final, attendance.
Really nice professor who is engaging and makes class interesting.
A pretty good prof, I have taken her courses for years. The only complaint is the occasionally boring lecture and very slow at grading course work and responding to emails.
You can tell she really wants her students to be successful. Is very easy to talk to and responds quickly to emails. A real great prof!

rComments: seminar course, structured so each student presents on an article once and is a discussant once. students are presenting 85% of the class. Nice to get to know students. Seminar, discussant, book review, attendance and participation, essay statement, final paper. A LOT of work and a lot of content. Tough marker. Nice, smart, funny lady. Good advice.

Super kind prof, I always say you are able to tell right away if a prof cares for her students, and Ms. Aucoin not only cares for the academic careers of her students, but also the sanity of them when leaving UOttawa.
She's really nice and reasonable about extensions and making up assignments.

rComments: Poor on all fronts. Boring, incoherent, poor structure to the course. To finish it all off she said a number of times we'd have a certain question on the final exam, and it wasn't there.
